		</font>
		<hr size="1">"I would get aggro whenever I would go near the mob"</P><P>Of course you were.  Pets are automatically at the bottom of the hate list, and a NPC will only go after the pet if it is the only thing within melee range on its list.  As soon as you got close enough to the hit the NPC, the pet no longer qualified as a valid target.</P><P>And I have to agree with the others.  You weren't increasing the rate at which experience was gained in any appreciable amount, so for a minor bit of effort, you were getting 50% of the experience.  On the other hand, from what I understand of how pets work with experience, the pet was getting 50% anyway for doing all the damage, you and beastlord were splitting the remaining 50%.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
